window.bookSummaryJSON = "<p><i>THE INTERNATIONAL BESTSELLER</i></p> <p><b>From the world-leaders in strategic thinking and the multi-million copy bestselling authors of </b><b><i>Thinking Fast and Slow</i></b><b> and </b><b><i>Nudge</i></b><b>, the next big book to change the way you think. </b>&nbsp;</p> <p>We like to think we make decisions based on good reasoning–and that our doctors, judges, politicians, economic forecasters and employers do too. In this groundbreaking book, three world-leading behavioural scientists come together to assess the last great fault in our collective decision-making: noise.</p> <p>We all make bad judgements more than we think. <i>Noise</i> shows us what we can do to make better ones.</p> <p><b>PLEASE NOTE: When you purchase this title, the accompanying PDF will be available in your Audible Library along with the audio.</b>&nbsp;</p>"; 
